The city of Calgary, Alberta, Canada found itself in the grip of a dire situation as a special weather alert was issued on Tuesday, warning residents about poor air quality and reduced visibility. The alarming conditions were a result of tinder-dry weather and shifting winds, which elevated the risk of spreading wildfires in the oil-producing province of Alberta.

According to the provincial government, a staggering 90 wildfires were currently active in Alberta, with 23 of them completely out of control. This dire situation has forced approximately 20,000 people to evacuate their homes, seeking safety elsewhere. The impact of the fires reached even further, affecting the oil and gas industry, causing several producers to shut down operations. At one point, a significant 319,000 barrels of oil equivalent per day, accounting for 3.7% of national production, were forced to cease.

@DeniseHenwood, a resident of Calgary, captured the devastating conditions on video on 16th May, 2023 and shared her experience. In her footage, she revealed the surrounding atmosphere filled with smoke, highlighting the poor air quality. "Woke up smelling smoke INSIDE the house. You can barely step outside. Burns eyes, throat, ugh, getting worse by the minute," she lamented.

On May 8th, 2023, Kingsland, a suburb of Auckland, New Zealand, experienced an unusual flooding event that caused some disruption to the traffic flow but created a rare spectacle for onlookers. The northwest motorway overbridge at Bond Street was submerged in water, creating a surreal sight for drivers who passed through it.

According to eyewitness accounts, the flooding was caused by heavy rainfall that had been pouring down in the area for several hours. The water level on the overbridge rose quickly, creating a layer of water that was about 20 meters above the motorway. While the flooding caused some inconvenience to the traffic, there were no reports of accidents or major disruptions.

@AndiBeeeee, a local resident who captured the flooding on video, shared her experience on social media. She described the sight as rare and fascinating, saying, "Not often you get flooding 20m above a motorway." Her video showed cars moving slowly on the flooded overbridge, with water splashing up against their wheels.

In Lincolnshire, UK, a weather enthusiast and avid photographer, @loki_weather, recently captured a captivating video of a funnel cloud swirling above his house in South Lincolnshire. The mesmerizing footage, shared on social media, has been making waves as people marvel at the sheer power and beauty of nature.

The video, taken on May 11th, 2023, between the towns of Grantham and Peterborough, provides a rare glimpse of a funnel cloud forming and swirling majestically in the sky. With a timestamp of approximately 11:50, the footage showcases the intensity and spectacle of this meteorological phenomenon.

@loki_weather, known for his keen eye for atmospheric events, expressed his excitement over the captivating sighting. He commented, "Look at this fantastic funnel cloud I captured over my house in South Lincolnshire!"
